{"title_page": "Mike King (radio announcer)", "text_new": "{{short description|American radio broadcaster}}\n{{ Other people|Mike King}}\n'''Michael Wayne \"Mike\" King'''<ref>{{cite video|first1=Mike|last1=King|first2=Dan|last2=Wheldon|authorlink2=Dan Wheldon|date=October 20, 2011|title=IndyCar Weekly: October 20, 2011&nbsp;\u2013 Dan Wheldon in his own words|url=http://plus.autosport.com/free/feature/3968/dan-wheldon-in-his-own-words/|medium=Radio broadcast|publisher=[[Haymarket Group|Haymarket Publications]]; [[IndyCar]]|accessdate=March 3, 2012|time=23:30\u201324:45}}</ref> (born in [[Virginia]]) is an American [[radio personality|radio broadcaster]], who is best known for being the chief announcer of the [[Indianapolis Motor Speedway Radio Network]] and [[Indy Racing League]] between 1996 and 2013.<ref name=\"Resigns\">{{cite news|url=http://www.indystar.com/article/20131028/SPORTS0107/310280038/IndyCar-get-new-Voice-500-Mike-King-resigns|first=Curt|last=Cavin|work=[[The Indianapolis Star]]|publisher=Karen Crotchfelt; [[Gannett Company]]|date=October 28, 2013|accessdate=October 29, 2013|title=IndyCar to get new 'Voice of the 500' as Mike King resigns}}</ref>\n\nHe began his announcing career at [[Campbell University]], his alma mater, where he was studying to become a minister. He worked as a sports writer for several [[North Carolina]] newspapers, and worked as sports information director at [[Campbell University]] from 1981\u20131982. He started on television in [[Greenville, North Carolina]], then took over as sports director at [[WTHI-TV]] in [[Terre Haute, Indiana]].\n\nIn 1995, King joined the [[Indianapolis Motor Speedway Radio Network]] as a pit reporter. King took over as chief announcer of [[Indy Racing League]] events in 1996, whereas [[Bob Jenkins]] remained chief announcer of the [[Indianapolis 500]]. In 1999, Jenkins departed the radio network, and King was elevated to chief announcer of the [[Indy 500]]. King remained in this position until the end of 2013, when he tendered his resignation.<ref name=\"Resigns\"/> He was replaced by [[Paul Page]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indystar.com/story/sports/motor/indy-car/2013/12/02/paul-page-returns-as-indy-500s-voice/3812917/|first=Curt|last=Cavin|work=[[The Indianapolis Star]]|publisher=Karen Crotchfelt; [[Gannett Company]]|date=December 2, 2013|accessdate=December 2, 2013|title=Paul Page returns as Indy 500's voice}}</ref>\n\n==Personal==\nHe was a partial owner of the [[Terre Haute Action Track]].<ref name=\"TribuneStar03012008\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tribstar.com/sports/local_story_061001422.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130105003353/http://www.tribstar.com/sports/local_story_061001422.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-05 |title=Promoters rev up Action Track schedule |last=Pearson |first=Craig |date=2008-03-01 |publisher=[[Tribune-Star]] |accessdate=2008-06-20 }}</ref> for three years, before selling it.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Bob Jenkins]]| title=Radio voice of the<br>[[Indianapolis Motor Speedway Radio Network|Indianapolis 500]]| \nyears=[[1999 Indianapolis 500|1999]]\u2013[[2013 Indianapolis 500|2013]] | after=[[Paul Page]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Indy 500}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:King, Mike}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American sports announcers]]\n[[Category:Motorsport announcers]]\n[[Category:People from Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n", "text_old": "{{ Other people|Mike King}}\n'''Michael Wayne \"Mike\" King'''<ref>{{cite video|first1=Mike|last1=King|first2=Dan|last2=Wheldon|authorlink2=Dan Wheldon|date=October 20, 2011|title=IndyCar Weekly: October 20, 2011&nbsp;\u2013 Dan Wheldon in his own words|url=http://plus.autosport.com/free/feature/3968/dan-wheldon-in-his-own-words/|medium=Radio broadcast|publisher=[[Haymarket Group|Haymarket Publications]]; [[IndyCar]]|accessdate=March 3, 2012|time=23:30\u201324: