bstar.com/sports/local_story_061001422.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130105003353/http://www.tribstar.com/sports/local_story_061001422.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-05 |title=Promoters rev up Action Track schedule |last=Pearson |first=Craig |date=2008-03-01 |publisher=[[Tribune-Star]] |accessdate=2008-06-20 }}</ref> for three years, before selling it.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box | before=[[Bob Jenkins]]| title=Radio voice of the<br>[[Indianapolis Motor Speedway Radio Network|Indianapolis 500]]| \nyears=[[1999 Indianapolis 500|1999]]\u2013[[2013 Indianapolis 500|2013]] | after=[[Paul Page]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Indy 500}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:King, Mike}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:American sports announcers]]\n[[Category:Motorsport announcers]]\n[[Category:People from Terre Haute, Indiana]]\n", "name_user": "NASCARfan0548", "label": "safe", "comment": "Importing Wikidatashort description: \"American radio broadcaster\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mike_King_(radio_announcer)"}
